  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "- Tokens sent to `address(0)` can not be transferred anymore, they are effectively out of the supply\r\n- Transferring tokens to `address(0)` is a very common implementation of a `burn` function in popular ERC20 frameworks\r\n- The current definition is not defined explicitly and is open to interpretation, recommend a more explicit definition\r\n\r\ne.g\r\n\r\nChange\r\n> Returns the total token supply.\r\n\r\nto\r\n> Returns the sum of all account balances excluding `address(0)`\r\n\r\nA simple example implementation:\r\n\r\n    function totalSupply() public view returns (uint) {\r\n        return _totalSupply - balances[address(0)];\r\n    }\r\n",
