    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "ERC20 as a standard is final and thus cannot be changed.  There are already tokens out there that don't account for balances in `address(0)` and they are ERC20.  This change would make it so those tokens are suddenly not ERC20 tokens.\r\n\r\nI recommend either creating a new ERC that extends ERC20, or providing your feedback to some of the new token standards that are being worked on.  FWIW, I believe ERC-777 already does the right thing in this regard.",
